# shadcn/ui Component Library

This project uses **shadcn/ui** as the primary UI component library for all interface elements.

## Configuration

The project is configured with shadcn/ui using the **"new-york"** style variant. See [components.json](mdc:components.json) for the complete configuration.

- **Style**: new-york
- **Components path**: `@/components/ui`
- **Utils path**: `@/lib/utils` (see [utils.ts](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts))
- **Icon library**: Lucide React
- **CSS Variables**: Enabled with neutral base color

## Component Installation

When you need a shadcn/ui component that isn't already installed, use this command:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

### Common Components
Examples of frequently used components:
- `npx shadcn@latest add button`
- `npx shadcn@latest add input`
- `npx shadcn@latest add form`
- `npx shadcn@latest add card`
- `npx shadcn@latest add dialog`
- `npx shadcn@latest add toast`
- `npx shadcn@latest add label`
- `npx shadcn@latest add separator`

## Usage Guidelines

1. **Always use shadcn/ui components** for all UI elements instead of creating custom components from scratch
2. **Import components** from `@/components/ui/[component-name]`
3. **Customize components** by modifying the generated files in `src/components/ui/` if needed
4. **Use the cn() utility** from [utils.ts](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts) for conditional class merging
5. **Follow Tailwind CSS classes** for styling, which are pre-configured to work with shadcn/ui

## Available Components

Check the [shadcn/ui documentation](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) for a complete list of available components.

## Best Practices

### Component Composition
- Compose complex UI from multiple shadcn/ui primitives
- Keep custom components minimal - prefer shadcn/ui variants
- Use component props for customization before adding custom CSS

### Styling with cn()
```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

// Good: Composing classes conditionally
<Button className={cn("w-full", isLoading && "opacity-50")} />

// Good: Merging with custom classes
<Card className={cn("border-2", className)} />
```

### Forms and Validation
- Use `form` component with React Hook Form for complex forms
- Combine `label`, `input`, and form field components
- Always provide proper accessibility attributes

### Theming
- Modify CSS variables in [globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) for theme changes
- Use semantic color tokens (e.g., `primary`, `secondary`, `destructive`)
- Dark mode is automatically supported via CSS variables

### Common Patterns

#### Loading States
```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Loader2 } from "lucide-react"

<Button disabled={isLoading}>
  {isLoading && <Loader2 className="mr-2 h-4 w-4 animate-spin" />}
  Submit
</Button>
```

#### Dialog Pattern
```tsx
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogHeader, DialogTitle, DialogTrigger } from "@/components/ui/dialog"

<Dialog>
  <DialogTrigger asChild>
    <Button>Open Dialog</Button>
  </DialogTrigger>
  <DialogContent>
    <DialogHeader>
      <DialogTitle>Dialog Title</DialogTitle>
    </DialogHeader>
    {/* Dialog content */}
  </DialogContent>
</Dialog>
```

#### Data Display
```tsx
import { Card, CardContent, CardDescription, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card"

<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
    <CardDescription>Description</CardDescription>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    {/* Card content */}
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

